yeah another popular kid here.


so right off the bat we need to know what bayes theorem is?

P(A|B) = P(B|A) Ã— P(A) / P(B)

and thus bayesian inference is statistical inference in which bayes
theorem is used to provide the probability of the outcomes under
consideration. 


















